description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Activity Facilitator &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity for an Activity Facilitator has arisen, to work on Aldervale Ward at Hopewood Park.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post would be an excellent opportunity for staff who are interested in facilitating the delivery of therapeutic activity within a male High Dependency Unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You would be supporting patients in identifying and carrying out both individualised and ward based group activities. You would also be expected to take an active role in the implementation of Talk 1st and the Safe Ward interventions. The post holder would work closely with the occupational therapy team and as part of the wider ward team, receiving regular supervision and peer support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited from candidates who possess excellent communication and interpersonal skills and the enthusiasm and passion to embed and develop therapeutic activity. You must have a strong commitment to the delivery of high quality, safe, patient care and be a good role model in reflecting the Trusts Core Values. You will be provided with training opportunities to develop your knowledge and skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be required to work flexibly to meet the needs of service users which may include working extended hours over 7 days a week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you require any further information or wish to have an informal discussion about what we have to offer please see details below directing you to the point of contact:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
